reviews:
The only positive points for staying at the Citadines Eiffel Tower is it’s location (convenient metro just in front) and spacious rooms for Parisian standards.

However, there was too much noise we could hear footsteps from neighboring rooms, from the metro and construction. VERY poor customer service: at check in empty shower gels and when asked to refill it wasn’t done. Uncomfortable beds and pillows… and to top it all terrible attitude from the receptionist …. That just sealed our opinion for never coming back to this hotel!
VERY important to note that unlock all other hotels housekeeping is at an extra charge and has to be pre booked 24 hours in advance !! We’ve been to other apartment hotels and never had this sort of service!

Liked: The location is excellent, just opposite the Metro Station. It's just about 10mins walk away from Eiffel Tower. The noise from the trains passing by was very mild and tolerable. Didn't disturb us particularly. The room floor was also very clean. Our room was on the 5th floor. They have 7 floors but the 7th floor is for studio rooms. We booked an apartment room (with Eiffel Tower view) as we had 4 pax (2 adults and 2 children). Wifi was great and stable. Kitchen had a stove, kitchen utensils and microwave. We were greeted by Asian-looking gentleman during check-in. We didn't get his name but he went out of his way to explain regarding the amenities available. He also helped us to call a restaurant for reservation although the restaurant was fully booked. There's a lovely French bakery called Merci Jerome nearby with beautiful selection of sweet and savoury pastries.

Disliked · The toilet was separate from the shower room. Could've provided with more rubbish bags as we stayed there for 6 days. Although these are only very minor issues

This hotel has amazing views of the Eiffel Tower, but the service was terrible. Housekeeping never showed up to clean our rooms. Much worse, the staff double-charged us. Imagine noticing your credit card has an extra mistaken $1,700 charge for two rooms. The staff refunded the second mistaken charge a couple days later - at a worse exchange rate, causing us to lose $50 or so for their error. Now they refuse to respond to fix this situation. I would not recommend this hotel.

This hotel was everything it said it’d be. It felt like a cute little European apartment. Large room/shower! I opted for the room with a view & it looked just like the pictures. It is right across from the metro, so that’s where the noise would come from. Free coffee & water in the lobby. Definitely would recommend :)

Perfect place if you want central location to discover Paris on foot. Easy tube access from airport and located in fantastic location. Staff is also very helpful and always ready to recommend good place to eat. Rooms have all you need and are clean, breakfast is typical of French hotels.

We arrived at the Hotel at 10am, check in was supposed to start from 3pm. 'Nes' (I hope I got her name right) saw us from the counter and offered us early check in, free of charge.

My friends and I booked 2 rooms from this Aparthotel for 3 nights. Both rooms were clean and spacious, with great view of the Eiffel Tower too (around half). Do take note that you have to select the right room type when booking tho, some room types do not face the Eiffel Tower. The room has cooking utensils, water heater works great, even the tap has hot water (and I really mean hot water). The only tiny drawback about this hotel is the lack of slippers.

Thermostat works well for my room, with options to cooling and heating the room. The rooms can get pretty dry during the night. Some rooms came with balcony (mine did), but it's pretty dirty outside so do take note. There is free coffee/hot coco at the hotel lobby, along with 2 vending machines selling snacks and some salad.

Location is great. Metro is just across the street. McDonald's is right beside the main lobby, with Monoprix and Franprix across the road too. Monoprix has a bakery and a food section selling sushi and microwavable food on the first floor, and a supermarket on the second floor.

Overall very pleasant stay indeed.

We booked this hotel very last minute when our plans changed and we rerouted to spend a couple of nights in Paris. The hotel itself is better suited for longer stays and is more equivalent to an American extended-stay with a kitchenette. We didn't use the appliances and really just needed a place to sleep and somewhere to use as a launching point for some sightseeing. It is well-within walking distance to major attractions. There is a fabulous Thai restaurant within the block and we actually went there both nights, it was that good. Although convenient, the biggest complaint is the noise from the next door subway station. A train came rumbling through every couple of minutes and my white noise app couldn't mask it at night. Overall a decent stay for our needs, but probably would not return.

This hotel was in a perfect area. Thw rooms are small, so dont expect American style rooms. But we only slept there and showered. So it was perfect. Coffee is provided in the lobby. They offer breakfast for a small cost. We didn't try it. My husband got the room with the view of the Effiel Tower. Couldn't have been a better choice. The hotel was about a 5 min scooter ride to the tower as well. McDonald's is not the same in france, so I wouldn't recommend going to the one by the hotel. The bakery was excellent as well as the other restaurants around. I can't wait to go back!

We stayed in serviced apartments managed by Ascott group throughout Asia and their services have alawys been good. However, we can’t say the same for Citadines Tour Eiffel Paris.

Check in - Process was transactional. Asked for our passport and payment then gave us the room keycard. Different from other Ascott group check in which will provide local info.

Room - We received a pre check-in page for us to put in our request. We requested for a quiet room and what we got was probably the noisiest room… facing the metro track and traffic. The room floor was also dirty (I wore white socks and my socks were dirty after walking around the room) and we found plastic lying on the floor from previous guests.

Housekeeping & towel change - We were informed about there is no housekeeping (in a “you should know that” attitude) & received a few versions about how we get our towels changed.

Staff - The morning shift staff is friendlier than the midnight shift staff. There is male staff whom we encountered twice(after 10pm) whom was not happy about us asking questions at all.

Location - convenient as near to lots of eateries and metro.

We have stayed here on every Paris visit for the last decade or more. Previously, we had found the staff charming and very friendly. This time they were merely efficient. When we rent in an apartment hotel, which this pretends to be, we plan to do some of our own cooking, especially in France where there is so much good food available and in this case a market steps from the front door on Wednesdays and Sundays. These units are so poorly equipped that this is virtually impossible. Even then, there were shortages of what was supposed to be available. One teaspoon for two people? One coffee mug for two people? Two small glasses, which is less than you usually get in an ordinary hotel room. The studio rooms are adequate and well insulated for sound, even those at the front a few feet meters from the metro trains. It is extremely convenient for three Metro lines and lots of restaurants. A great place to stay, but as a self-catering apartment it is a dismal failure. We bought some of our own utensils and containers to get by. For example, they have a microwave but no containers to microwave anything in!

Pictures definitely don’t tell the whole story here.
The staff was great and friendly. The view of the tower was also spectacular. But….
Once you look down, the metro station is right there. It’s like a scene out of Rocky 1. The train goes by all night, so if you don’t have enough drinks to knock you out, it will keep you up all night.
The mattress was so broken down, it was only half the depth that it should be, not to mention the spring in my back all night long. The mold in the bathroom was disgusting. There is no ventilation or fans to keep it from growing.
Bed never gets made or new towels (towels were like a 1 ply toilet paper). No coffee maker in the room, have to bring your cups from the room down to the lobby to get your coffee.
We were scared to try the breakfast, so skipped it for our entire stay. Laundry is do your own.
Far from the 4.5 rating. Definitely a 2 to 2.5.

Arrived at hotel and walked into acceptable lobby.
Checking in was told there was no room cleaning, even we were staying several days. You can get new towels, also toilet paper, by coming down to the lobby. Then when we got to our room, what a shock, nothing like the pictures they have on there web site. The place really needed an update, old everything, no pictures on the walls. No closet to hang your clothes. No place to put your suitcase accept at the bottom of your bed. Bathroom dirty, towels so thin you could see through them. We had a beautiful view of the above ground tram railway. Not worth the money. By the way, I loved Paris and will come back but won’t make this mistake again.

We booked the hotel only for one night after coming from Disneyland as we had a day before heading back. Really convenient location and we booked the room with the eiffel tower view a bit pricey but I guess it's worth it also we had the family room so was very spacious and had a microwave , fridge,dish washer, pots,and pans almost like a home away from home. The metro is literally at the door step and there is a direct train to Arc de triumph and the eiffel tower is walking distance. Now the metro being so cloase also has its disadvantages. You will hear the metro passing by and also feel the vibration. Its was not a game changer for me however was a lottle annoying at the beginning but grew on us a few hours later. Plenty of food options with McDonald's literally the next building.

The staff are extremely friendly and very accommodating. Now for the possible improvements. The breakfast is over priced especially because its a very small selection. Unless Breakfast is included don't pay for it. The rooms are very clean but can be a little modern. Just beig picky here they can have a few more TV channels in English. But overall a good hotel with well placed in terms of location and also access to food options. Good view of the eifel tower if you chose the right room that is.

Stayed 4 nights at a one bedroom apartment, kids slept on the sofa bed, no issue at all. Apartment was clean had a full kitchen even though small but it worked out good for us.

Our room had the Eiffel tower view on the 6th floor, you can see the lights at night. So beautiful. Even though it was in front of the metro line, we weren't too bothered about the noise as some reviews mentioned.

On sunday morning there was a local market, we spent some time there buying artisan croissants..very delicious.

Also there is McDonald's right besode the hotel, and Monprix supermarket across the street, very convenient for families. We also had breakfast at a local cafe across the road, I forgot the name but I recommend the green cafe as it was cheaper than the other ones, and the breakfast set was good, omelets, croissants, baguette, jam, OJ and coffee/tea for €11.

Will definitely stay again if I visit Paris 🙂

This hotel was perfect for two couples. The configuration of the rooms is such that both couples will have privacy, although one of the couples will be sleeping on a sofa bed. The mini kitchen in the apartment has everything you could possibly need, and the bathrooms are configured so that the toilet is in a separate room from the sink and shower, also allowing for a bit more privacy if more than one couple is sharing an apartment. There is complimentary water and coffee available in the lobby. The only reasons I am giving this hotel an average rating is due to room cleanliness/repair issues (there was blood spattered all over a curtain in the room, and one of the bathroom doors would not close properly due to the fact that it had obviously been bashed in at some point) and the fact that they have the air conditioning turned off. You can turn it on and hear it functioning, but there is no cool air being circulated. Depending on what time of year you are visiting, Paris is much too hot to not have at least some functioning air conditioning, even the lobby was a bit stifling.

the location is very good you have everything next to the hotel ! walk distance to the Eiffel Tower to make a jogging in the morning.
next to Champs Elysees by walk

when I check in at 22:00 the receptionist was not nice he didn't say hello directly give me to sign the form and tell me how much I need to paid!
As director of the reception where I live, it was not a good reception (and it has nothing to do if I check in at 12:00 or 10:00 p.m.) and I was really very disappointed! He did not explain to me for breakfast (despite that it was not included in my reservation but if I wanted to take it?) and that there is a coffee machine for hotel guests, if there is one passwords for wifi ect.....all i need to have
Even during my stay of 1 week the receptionists were not so helpful with me when I asked for a service (so I no longer wanted to ask what it was) and really know it's a shame!
Even for my check out I asked to put my suitcases in the Baggage room, they made me happy that I put it!!!!
in the bathroom the soap was already used everything was old
badly hanging curtain, dirty curtains ect....
i will never come back to this Apart Hotel

This hotel was recommended by our Travel Advisor for our first trip to Paris and did not disappoint. The location is wonderful and it is a very easy walk up to the Eiffel Tower. The front desk staff was very helpful and kind with suggestions and directions especially Valentina!

The rooms are a great size and having the apartment style set up is wonderful. We had an amazing view from our rooms and could not have asked for more to make our little home away from home feel great while we were there!

This was a "big birthday" trip for 3 senior friends. We stayed 7 nights and found the hotel very safe and convenient. Our apartment (312) had a view of the Eiffel Tower and was a good layout with K bdr and a split pull-out sofa in living area, plus table/4 chairs, mini-kitchen and split bath. It was small, but larger than we expected given typical European hotel room sizes. We didn't eat at the hotel; bought pastries/yogurt/berries/cheeses/wine nearby. The metro was just across the street, so perfect for convenience; some noise but didn't bother us at night. Many cafes, small shops, plus a yummy bakery nearby. The staff was very helpful, especially Valentina who did our check-in and continued to help us throughout with metro assistance, suggestions, etc always with a smile.

Daily cleaning not available , clear own garbage , breakfast is a bit overpriced , reception staff is very helpful .
We stayed for 3 nights - it was decent , supermarket next door , MC Donalds , sushi , next door , diagonally opp restaurant awesome food , very good location …… we walked to Eiffel Tower 15/20 mins max .

We were at the hotel for 5 nights and it was a great location to be at! With 2 kids, there was enough room and it was a spacious apartment. Loved going to the nearby cafes, walked to Eiffel Tower in the evening, and strolled around at the bakeries, everything was within walking distance and I highly recommend the place! It was very clean and safe!

Unfortunately not the best of stays at Citadines and quite upset. We arrived at the hotel around 11am to check our bags in and pay the full amount, we then returned at 4pm to check into our room. We were told to take a seat and waited nearly half an hour without being told anything except 'someone is checking it', but it was very obvious the room was not cleaned as the women can down with a cloth and spray to tell them its okay! We received free breakfast the next morning as an apology what helped but I preferred if they were more honest about the room not being ready. When we got to our room we impressed by the view, but unfortunately that quickly changed when we realized we were right next to a metro station. This was quite loud every night and extremely disappointing for the price we payed. It was my partners birthday which she made them aware, the hotel didn't say anything about this, I understand it isn't mandatory but it does go a long way to show respect. When we checked into our next hotel they were much more friendly and expressed their interest in the birthday. The staffs English wasn't so strong, I am in belief this is not a hotel I'd suggest to a foreign tourist, this seems like a much more local hotel with the guests. On checkout the women on reception was not made aware of our complimentary breakfast but in the end took our word on it. We got back home to realize we left two items on the bed. We emailed the hotel and didn't receive a reply, so I called them for them to say no we haven't got the item, when it was left on the bed quite obviously left, so the cleaner must of binned it and failed to admit it was there. They said they couldn't check properly till Wednesday, which didn't make any sense as they must of already been in the room for the next guests? There seems to be many problems with communication in the hotels staff, after checking into our second hotel it made us upset to not spend the two nights at this place instead. If you are on a budget and want something close to the Eiffel tower then maybe this is an option but unfortunately I cannot see myself staying here again.

After paying in full at check in I was told the room
would be ready “in 20 minutes”. Rather than standing in a cramped reception we went across the road for a coffee (husband and 2 small
Kids). On our return we were given our keys.. go to our 1 bed apartment to find dirty towels on floor of bathroom and a suitcase and food wrappers in bedroom !!! We go back to reception and complete chaos. No one knew what was going on or who was in our room. 4 ladies in reception making many phone calls and looking intently at computers and refusing to give me any information, apologies or assurances. My 2 children extremely tired and becoming increasingly upset. After 2 hours from (from start of check in) manager finally appears and confirms no hotel room available for us. I had to frantically Google a new hotel room and make own arrangements to ensure I had somewhere to sleep.

This place has become our home in Paris. We know the area very well as we lived around for some time, and staying here allows us to reconnect with our old area. The front desk staff is amazing, and the property is very well kept. We had another Eiffel Tower view studio, and waking up to that spectacular view was amazing. The studio was very spacious and had all the basics. The hotel is well connected by Metro and Bus and you can get anywhere very quick. Overall a recommended place to stay.

I want to start by saying , it’s this was one of the best vacations ever for me and my little one and the hospitality of the hotel staff just made it so much better! We arrived in Paris extremely early and they were so accommodating, on top of that the ladies and gentlemen who work the front desk are so pleasant and nice! There is one girl that stood out , i didn’t get her name but she has black hair , she made my daughter feel so special and she even volunteered to be our photographer when she saw me struggling to get a good picture! I will definitely return to Paris and this will be where I stay.

Other major points for the hotel - it’s not really a hotel but apartments like which have more room.

Also location is a blessing, there are so many shops ,McDonald, pharmacies and super markets right around.

The residence is also a 10 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower. Can’t beat that .

What a fantastic stay, and great value for money from a very caring and professional team. Amazing views from a good-sized room, bright and spacious with full amenities like a small studio with kitchenette, TV, wifi, safe etc... was a real delight. The hotel is super well situated in the midst of town, with convenient shopping, great restaurants and the metro, surprisingly quiet, right at your door. A traveller's dream!!! Bravo and thank you everyone.

Wow, wow, wow, just come back from a weekend trip to Paris, I LOVED this hotel, the bed was so comfy, the room was super clean, we had so many amenities like a kitchen area, tv, wifi, safe etc. We had the best room in the hotel by far, it was absolutely perfect, my highlight was watching the Eiffel Tower lights from lying in bed! I can’t thank the staff enough for giving us that room, the staff were so polite and helpful, such an amazing hotel!

Had a Eiffel tower balcony view room and the view did not disappoint was absolutely amazing and so nice to see everyone from the room or balcony. Staff at reception were nice and was no problem in checking out 1 hour later for free. Very clean hotel.

Truly enjoyed my 3 night stay here. Modern, spacious, clean room with amazing views of the Eiffel Tower, which was the main reason why I booked this hotel.
Great location, near 3 subway lines , bakery, supermarket, restaurants.
Would gladly book again.

I paid for a room with a view of the Tower Eiffel, (as I saw in the picture of the room) but neither from the bed or the table, I could see that, I needed to go to the balcony to see it. The option of breakfast was terrible and expensive. The fire alarm rang in the corridor for nothing. I stayed in another hotel days before that was much better and much cheaper.
I don't recommend it to anyone. it doesn't worth the price.

We arrived early after travel difficulties, and were not surprised to find our room wasnt available early. We were exhausted and had an evening appointment, so getting in at least on time and having time to clean up and rest was important. After 4 hours wait, knowing we were available, and well after our room was supposed to be free it still wasnt ready, they simply coldly said "no, its not ready yet, try again in a half hour." No apology for running late, nothing. When we finally got in later it was not the twin bedroom we reserved, and the bedside lights didnt even work, infact one was falling off of the wall. The bed was very uncomfortable. There were no USB chargers, and for one person to read in bed all the lights had to be left on. The curtain was hanging with several hooks off also. Aside from this the simple efficiency apartment was adequate, and had a view of te Eiffel Tower as promised. The promised available breakfast however, one of the reasons we had stayed here, was not available "we just have a bag" they shrugged. This a year and a half into COVID, when many hotels have been able to offer lovely COVID safe breakfast options. They should have updated their site to indicate that this was not available, so as not to deceive customers. The doors to the hotel are always locked, often front desk was unmanned, and when it was, with one exception in 4 days, no one ever even bothered to look up in greeting, while guests were entering or leaving, even though they were never with another guest. Other than one evening desk worker (a young man), everyone was cold and indifferent, and one middle aged man even actively refused to help answer questions myself and another guest had one evening. He just waived us off rudely and went back to eating in the back. Before you say-"Well, this in France, that is how people are", in every SINGLE shop, restuarant, tour, museum, everyone was friendly, and said "bonjour, bon soir", etc, everyone except our own hotel. Unless you just want an uncomfortable bed in a convenient area, and dont care about non-functioning things in a room and no promised breakfast available, and a cold, detatched, uncaring staff, I recommend staying elsewhere. They really made my daughters graduation trip less enjoyable. There are many other places to stay.

My interactions with this hotel was far from favorable. If you want to stay somewhere hospitable, avoid this place at all costs. I called ahead and asked for my reservation to be moved by a day because of flight delays that put me back a day. After the hotel attendant confirmed that there WAS room and he’d “do all that he can to help” but because I booked through Booking.com, I’d have to go through them. Which is okay! He tried guilt-tripping me talking about Booking.com’s commission fees -which has nothing to do with me.
And so I asked Booking.com and they said they’d be happy to ask the hotel considering that me arriving in the country a day late was out of my control. The same hotel person denied my request, even after taking my money and confirming they have room.
Go elsewhere. There’s plenty of other options!

Came here during the 8pm curfew, the ample restaurants, supermarkets and bakeries around meant take-out and food delivery is no problem at all.

5 minutes walk to the Parc du Champ De Mars where the Eiffel Tower is.

We stayed at the Citadines Tour Eiffel during a 5-day visit to Paris. Chose this hotel because we used to live and work in this area so being in a familiar place was a must for us. Directly across the Metro station, you can get to any place in Paris in less than 40 minutes. The service was excellent and the studio was very cozy. But what we love the most was the view from our terrace. The stunning view of the Eiffel Tower reminded us the beauty of the city. We will stay here again whenever we visit Paris.

Check in at the hotel was relatively smooth. The deluxe room was spacious, clean and air-conditioned and offered an amazing view of the Eiffel tower.

The location is unbeatable- close to the metro and plenty of cafes and bistros. On the second night the flush of the toilet did not work, so when I advised reception, she was very curt and abrupt and said I had to wait 30 minutes before anyone could come solve my problems. I asked for an alternate room, but not a possibility. Please keep in mind this was already almost 9.30pm at night and I was ready to unwind after a very long day of walking in the Paris heat. A kind staff member showed up 30 minutes later and did a quick fix.

The kitchenette offers basic kitchen utensils, but bring your own coffee/tea. Additionally, I had to rewash some of the mugs and plates as they were a bit dirty and were chipped.

The biggest downside for me: There is NO housekeeping offered unless you want to fork out an exorbitant daily fee. If Citadines wants to use the name "hotel", then they really should be offering housekeeping and especially, in times of COVID, the least they could do was take out the garbage. I would recommend guests bring their own sanitizing solutions.

Citadines Grenelle is the ideal hotel to stay with a breathtaking view of Eiffel Tower.
The studio is spacious , spotlessly clean and it is equipped with a full kitchen . Located near supermarkets and shops with easy access to public transport.
A bit thank you to Mr Rabat for his outstanding hospitality.

I visited this hotel in 4 times, whenever visited this hotel , I was very satisfied with very kind employee / very good location / nice price
I am really recommend to visit this hotel to other person
of course, if i will have business in Paris, I will also visit this hotel again.
very nice hotel !!

We had a 2 night stopover here on our drive through France as the kids were desperate to see Paris. We chose the Citadines Tour Eiffel because of its central location and secure underground parking (we had bikes on the back of the car.) Parking was €30/night. The apartment was compact but had everything we needed and was spotlessly clean with a good shower. Double bed was very comfortable with a decent mattress. Sofa bed mercifully split into 2 so the kids didn’t spend all night fighting over who had rolled across the halfway line.

Management are clearly taking COVID precautions very seriously - single use pens to fill in the check in form, screens at reception, obligatory mask wearing in public areas, used key cards quarantined on check out and hand sanitiser freely available - so it felt like a safe place to stay. The reception staff were friendly and helpful (from a safe distance!)

I’d recommend for anyone wanting a centrally located apartment for a short stay in Paris. Easy walking distance to the Eiffel Tower and river and right next to La Motte Picquet Grenelle metro station with 3 metro lines. Monoprix supermarket directly opposite and plenty of places to eat and drink nearby (or a few stops on line 10 to the Latin Quarter for dinner.)

Check in process is a strange one, you have to sign up to something? But cannot check in without doing so?! Wifi works great, excellent room! Stunning view if you have an Eiffel Tower view room. Helpful staff, and Free Hot chocolate/coffee machine in lobby to help yourself at any time. Walking distance to the Eiffel Tower, and amazing little restaurant across the road with amazing staff. Will definitely return and definitely recommend.

wonderful stay wit a great view of Eiffel tower, and there is a supermarket very near, and dont forget the market. very good location with many restaurant. And there is walking distance to Eiffel tower .

The location of this hotel is easy accessible to literally everywhere. Public transportation is just nearby and walking distance to the Eiffel tower.

However, customer service at the hotel is extremely bad and feel unwelcome! There was an instance where I was standing in front of the two staff wanted to ask something, but they pretended inwwdnt there whilst continue to proceed with their conversation. It was totally unacceptable to me personally. No hospitality at all! Will never return to this hotel in the future!

Très bonne qualité de l'appartement. Personnel très sympathique. Emplacement idéal à Paris. Une machine à café dans le hall. We had a great time and enjoyed the whole City. ideal is that the next Metro Station is right in front of the Hotel.

Stayed one week. Very good location near metro stop, lots of restaurants and short walk to the Eiffel Tower. Friendly and helpful staff. Stayed in a very spacious studio with an excellent kitchen area.

I wanted a hotel in a good location on my recent visit. Not only was it in the best location, 4 blocks from the Eiffel tower, but it was clean and the staff was the friendliest! I'm a travel agent, so I'm picky, but I will definitely recommend this hotel.

Very friendly staff Mr. "RABAH"
Thanks to this I was able to check in very smoothly and accurately.
I also liked the first impression of Paris that came back every time. This is all thanks to Mr. RABAH.

- 위치가 좋아요. 바로 앞에 4개의 호선이 있는 메트로역이 있어서 어디로든 갈 수 있어요!
- 근처 빵집이나, 레스토랑이 많고 늦게까지도 치안이 괜찮은거 같아요.
- 근처에 까르푸, 모노프릭스 등 마트가 근접해있어요, (모노프릭스가 크고 종류가 더 많아요)
- 7층에 머물렀는데 에펠탑이 보이는 뷰라 너무 좋았습니다.
- 어메니티는 부족하니 챙겨오셔야 해요.
- 전자레인지, 오븐, 세탁기, 금고, 식기세척기, 냉장고, 다리미, 필요한 모든게 있어요.
- 총 7박했는데 중간에 청소 한번 해주셨어요.
- 필요한 수건이나 쓰레기는 2층인가 가서 가져올수도 버릴 수도 있었습니다.
- 세면대 물이 잘 안내려가더라구요
- 바로 앞에 메트로가 있어서 소음이 있긴한데 창문 닫으면 괜찮아요.

a great extraordinary location,a very energetic commercial area, you have a lot of nice restaurants and famous shopping stores also monoprix hypermarket is cross the corner, very comfy & clean studios fully equipped

Stayed at this hotel with my boyfriend on the next stop of our trip. Hotel was clean, staff was friendly and helpful. Room was a nice size and clean. The only reason I didn’t give it 5 stars is the AC didn’t really get cold. We were hot at night sleeping. Other than that I have nothing bad to say about this hotel.

Good value far a good sleep, near to centre just 1.1km to eifel.. its a short trip but i can sleep well in this hotel apart.. near the hotel you can find coffee shop and mini market.. danke well .. !!!

The staff here are so rude. We were waiting to talk to someone at reception & the person who was on duty was on a personal call, saw us waiting and didn’t get off their call to help us. We gave up and walked away.
On another occasion while staying here, we wanted to put things in the safe at the front desk. The person on duty sighed and said first of all that there was a safe in our room. We explained that online reviews from people on TripAdvisor said they had things stolen from the safe in their rooms. We were told by the receptionist this never happened!!
The breakfast at the hotel is terrible - don’t waste your money. It was poorly set out, the person duty in the breakfast room didn’t explain how things worked or where things were. We arrived 30 minutes after it was supposed to be open and it things were still being set up. The selection offered wasn’t good for what you’re charged.

We have stayed here several times and like it because of the convenience for the Metro (three lines) and the ambience of the neighbourhood. Because we like to make our own meals on some nights in Paris it is also convenient for a very good Monoprix supermarket across the street and even more so on Sundays and Wednesdays when there is a market under the elevated Metro line. There is the most amazing choice of any kind of food you wish – meat, poultry, fish, vegetables, fruits, cheese, bread and patisserie and some non-food items as well. Unfortunately, the kitchenettes in the Citadines are sorely deficient if you wish to do some serious cooking. Nevertheless, we buy a few extra items and prepare fabulous feasts on about half the evenings we are there and there is a boulangerie across the street where I can get our breakfast baguette for one Euro. Service at the desk is friendly and helpful and the studio apartments are rather small but just okay for two people.

My daughter and I had a wonderful week in this hotel! It’s very clean, staff is polite and helpful and the location is super convenient. Directly across from a metro station, lots of restaurants and shops within walking distance. We had a view of the Eiffel Tower in the distance. Lovely evening walks to the Eiffel Tower was an added bonus!

Family of four from US visiting Paris for first time. Location picked by travel agent. We would not choose to stay here again if opportunity arises.

Room: this location is more of an apartment than hotel especially thinking about some of the services you may expect in a hotel (housekeeping, room service). We had a spacious room with a bdrm with a king bed and a sofa sleeper in another room that folded out to 2 twin beds so it can sleep 4 comfortably. On arrival, the room was clean but there is no housekeeping and you have to get your own towels and supplies. If we wanted to stay in apartment, we would have used airbnb.

I have seen reviews about view of eiffel tower. well - we didnt have one. The location is near the Eiffel (15 min walk). Having the metro station across the street is convenient but if you have young children (stroller age) , you probably wont be using the metro much. Having a McDonalds and a grocery store (monoprix) nearby was useful. there are many places to eat as others have written in their reviews.

Customer service: adequate
Cleanliness: there was a definite odor to the hallways that was not pleasant (1st floor)
Breakfast: we did not participate
Noise: the disadvantage of being near a metro is the train rumbling by. But the main noise complaint was hearing all the flushing of the upper floors in our room. That was annoying.

Supplies: the kitchen was supplied with fridge, dishwasher, utensils/bowls. We didnt use these much during our 4 days there.

For our last night in Paris we booked Citadines for the Eiffel Tower views and were not disappointed. We were on the top floor (7) and had a little balcony, and could see the whole Eiffel Tower. Stunning. A bonus to have basic kitchen facilities, but don't expect a particularly warm welcome from the reception staff!

The hotel is located opposite to a metro station, which is very near to the Eiffel tower. Number of restaurants (Indian/ French), bars and pubs are available around the hotel. There is a McDonald's in the ground floor. Therefore whatever your taste you will be able to find.

best location.plenty of restaurants to choose only minuites away.unfortunately the best outdoor seating is taken up by smokers a lot of the time.easy 10 min stroll to the amazing Eiffel tower and the cruise boats along the seine river.train station across the road.we had aroom with a view of the Eiffel tower,a must.supermarket and café clothing across the road in the monoprix

I am a Citadines lover and stay in their hotels around the world. The Tour Eiffel location however, was not up to par.

The front desk staff were very rude every time we encountered them, especially at check in.

I would consider the location good but not great. We aren't big on public transportation, instead more about walking and the hotel was not great for walking. The bakery across the street with some of the best madeleines i've ever eaten made up for the hotel itself. The walk to the Eiffel tower was around 10-15 minutes and it was pleasant enough. There are some decent enough restaurants nearby.

The room was loud, very loud. We heard everything and everyone into the wee hours of the morning. The bed was uncomfortable. Not my favourite place to stay, sadly

We booked the room with the Eiffel Tower view which is very nice. The room is huge with a fair-sized kitchen and adequate kitchenware. The supermarket downstairs has many choice of food for selection. It is great for budgeted travelers to prepare meal on their own. Perfect Location, just right outside the metro exit and a walking distance to Eiffel Tower. Travelers may need to pay attention that the hotel does not provide cleansing service but it was totally fine for us since we only stayed for two nights. The room is very clean and you can get new towels if needed. Everything is satisfactory to me.

Great value. Comfortable. Air conditioner typical European. The front desk staff can be quirky at times but meet your needs. We didn’t have an Eiffel Tower “view” room, but could still see the top half of the tower which was perfect for the lights at night.

Great location to stay to visit Paris, close to Eiffel Tower across the road from a metro station and plenty of cafes and bars close by. Comfortable accommodation with all amenities and friendly staff.

the room is clean, but quite standard. good bed. wonderful staff. great location next to metro subway station. and good choices and variety of restaurants. the biggest downside was that the air conditioning was very weak - in public areas and inside room as well. the hotel itself as well as the room is not even in the same league as other 4 star hotels such as hyatt regency, le meridien or novotel in paris. even 3 star mercure hotels (as I have stayed at several in france) has better amenities and atmosphere than this citadines. am not sure how the hotel classified itself as 4 star when it’s actually 3 star.

The room was nice and standard, but what stood out was the perfect view of the Eiffel Tower from our room. The location was awesome: everything was in walking distance and it was across the street from the train station. There was also free continental breakfast every morning. Overall, I would definitely stay here again.

Excellent staff and location. In front of the Metro station. Availability of coffee 24 hours. Clean view of the tower on the 7th floor. Correct and varied breakfast. Good function of the air conditioning.

Hotel's location is excellent. There is a grocery store in one corner, several restaurants within blocks, metro right in front and an open market diagonally across. Places of interests are very accessible. The hotel is very clean and rooms are adequate and comfortable. Coffee and tea provided at the lobby is a plus.

A normal room with a nice eiffel tower view. The view was nice but one of my rooms smelt damp. the location of the hotel was great. There was a big mart near the hotel. I could see the white eiffel in my room.

Excellent location in the City of Paris. We had a view of the Eiffel Tower from our apartment room. An excellent small hotel close to fabulous French restaurants and a Farmers market across the street. A great place from which to enjoy Paris.

Great experience at this hotel! It is clean, room is spacious, staff is friendly and helpful and wonderful location. Visiting Paris for my daughter’s first international travel. This has been a great location for ease with metro across the street and lots of shops and restaurants near by.

Location : Nearby attractions such as the Eiffel Tower
Traffic : There are 3 subway lines, 80 bus stop, and many taxis.
Safety : There is no safety problem at the high street.
Shopping : Mongju Pharmacy, Korea Mart, Decatron are nearby.
A clean house, friendly staff ...
All satisfied!

We stayed 3days(26 ~ 29 May)
We consider effel view and covenience to go to tour sight.
This hotel coonnect to 3 metro lines.

We always saw effel in our room day and night.

We satisfied stay this hotel and recommend.

Great room, great location. We had a 1 bedroom and were upgraded to Eiffel tower view which was amazing! We were able to watch the light show from the room. The room was large enough that we didn't feel cramped at all. Bathroom was nice, as was the kitchen. I was also surprised to find a washer drier, as everything i had read is they were not available. So that was a pleasant surprise! Also location was perfect, a nice walk to the Eiffel tower, shops and restaurants. This is more of a local area then a tourist area, which i loved. Would stay here again for sure! Thanks for a great visit!

Very comfortable and cozy hotel near Effel Tower. If you want to have a good rest with sigtseeing, I wold reccomend you this hotel. There are cozy rooms with small kitchen full of equipment, good bathroom, clean towels and bed linen. It is very easy to go to different famous places from the hotel

The reception is very friendly and nice. Room is surprisingly better alot than our expectation! Its clean, spacious and comfortable! Will come back again if visit paris. Very good location as well (McD, Monoprix and alot more is jus less than 30second walk)

Reception: Maybe the week part of this apart hotel, the reception is ok but not as good and kind as some 4-5 stars hotels.
*You can get free choco or coffee all days anythime next to the reception :)

The location: Very good just in front of Grenelle metro station, is a studio so we just went to the monoprix shop in the corner to buy our food, perfect

The Room: Believe me, just pay the extra for the Eiffel view room, wooh, we were in the studio three days, to sleep every night seeing how the eiffel tower lights turned on and off in the early morning was great! what a way to go to sleep.

Will I come back? Very good option for Paris near the Eiffel tower, is not thattt close, but is near. The best is the view and the modern services of a studio

Suggestion:
If you plan to stay several days in Paris and close to the metro and everything like that, I will suggest this option seriously, you can save a lot with meals and is fun. Cool rememberings here :)
* high floor and eiffel view is a must.

I would highly recommend the Citadines Tour Eiffel. The location is perfect with the Metro right at the door, grocery store across the street, lots of restaurants in the close vicinity and a 20 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower. The rooms are spacious (we stayed in a studio), clean and well equipped. We had other reviews that complained about street noise but our room was facing onto Grenelle (with a lovely view of the Eiffel Tower) and we had our windows open the whole time and did not find it noisy. It is a lovely hotel in a great location.

This is the best place to stay in Paris! My family and I stay at this hotel every year and we absolutely love it! The staff is incredible! They are so warm and welcoming and kind! The rooms are terrific! They have everything you can possibly need! We travel as a big family with young children and the staff takes tremendous care of us! The views are gorgeous and everything about this place is absolutely magical!

Everything was just perfect. I stayed at the Room with a view tô Eiffel tower and it was amazing sleeping every night contemplating its beauty. Location was perfect: right in front train station, bus stop, several coffee shops, restaurants, super market, etc. Everything I needed I could have in walking distance, including Eiffel tower walking. The room was confortable, kitchen well equiped and a very Nice, clean and spacious bathroom. I would definetely stay again in this hotel When back in Paris. Highly recommend!

The location is very strategic. Near by shopping complex and just beside train station. Every Wednesday and Sunday morning, there is a morning market which sells fresh fruits, vegetables and seafood. There are also a lot of shops nearby.

While the location was good, the apartment was very tired and dated and smelt bad - in fact the smell permeated our suitcases and clothing and lasted our entire trip away. While the bed was comfortable the furniture in the lounge/dining room wasn't.

Be aware when booking this hotel that it is fully self-service - right down to changing your own towels. Location is very near the Eiffel Tower and Metro which can make it noisy in some rooms. Overall I was not impressed - the hotel is tired, it smells a bit, the beds aren't very comfy and staff surly.

Great hotel experience. Close location with metro line and very close to Eiffel Tower. Several shops around and supermarket directly across the street. Good service and comfortable room and large size.

Had recent stay at Citadines Tour Eiffel during our trip to ParisHad a great experience, very close to all tourist sites , great areaVery safe for families . Great restaurants, grocery stores , convenient stores

工作人員雖然服務周到，但酒店本身的裝潢以及一切設施都在廉價汽車賓館（還要是過時的廉價汽車賓館）的檔次。入住的人都應該是 1）沖著巴黎鐵塔景觀（只在最高的 6/F 和 7/F）和， 2）酒店的便利性而來的吧?

訂房的時候，我提早 18 日前 email confirm 並註明我的額外要求。雖然所分派房間可能受到多個因素影響，但我最後成功獲分配到頂層風景最好的一間轉角房間，擁有 L 型露台，一間可在不同角度，日與夜都能夠完美地擁抱巴黎鐵塔的房間!!!!!

切記，大前提是要在合適的時間提出合理的要求!!! 若你於 1 星期前提出，而該房間有其他旅客的話，酒店可能無法配合。若你兩個月之前提出，酒店亦沒有可能空著那房間等你。不過，你可以自訂酒店一日起每個月都聯絡一下酒店，這樣人家也可以有充分的時間為你預備。

得到酒店方面的配合，讓我就算只待在房內都能夠拍照拍到最後一刻才捨得出發去已預約的餐廳吃飯，酒店的員工當然功不可沒。在巴黎，比這間酒店更用心，更願意去服務旅客的酒店工作人員並不常見。

地點方面也是一流，3 條地鐵線，另加幾條巴士線（因為怕被打荷包，我很多時候避而不乘地鐵出市中心 1 、2 區而選搭巴士，搭巴士去老佛爺也安全方便）。酒店旁邊就是佔地兩層的中型超市，斜對面馬路更會在星期三、六有中大型市集（約有 40 多個排檔和地攤。另外 15 區因為不像其他區般擁有特色景點，所以地鋪租金相較其他區段低，這卻造就了一個食肆林立的美食創業區域，十分值得饕客探索。

酒店的設施雖要更新嗎? 陳舊到不能，絕對需要。需要更有效率的升降機維修公司嗎? 我住的 5 天當中其中 1 部升降機都封著，正在維修，絕對需要更換另一間維修公司。房內設備需要大更新嗎? 房內所有東西都像是 90 年代一般平價汽車旅館的陳設，沒設計沒風格，絕對需要大更新。

員工出色，但酒店的硬件也需要接軌才會讓客人回頭。以相同的價格，除非酒店大換妝吧，否則我想我並不會再回來。

(我選擇不貼照片，因為我不想其他人只看了我的照片便跑去訂房，完全忽略了這間旅店的重大缺點。)

Spent 3 nights here with my 3 Daughters. Loved the location right next to the metro! Rabah was most pleasant upon check-in. Spacious apartment with a view of the Eiffel Tower. Beds were comfortable and had everything we needed to fix breakfasts in the morning. Coffee machine in the lobby was pretty good and satisfied our wants. Nice market close by.
Even though you are a bit “out of town”, the metro makes it super easy to get where you want to be. Loved it and would stay here again!

If you are not looking for 5 star hotel service but a good apartment hotel, this is the place!Right in front of the apartment, you could enjoy Open-air Marche`and easy Gourmet shops.Metro station is also in front of apartment door!

Had read great reviews about this Hotel/Apts, yes, it is a good location, near the Metro and the Eiffel Tower, and good neighborhood. But, the purpose of hotel when you are traveling is a starting point and ending point to your day on vacation where you can recoup and refresh yourself for the night or the next day. This property is very "dated" and could use some "refreshing", the carpets are worn and the walls and door ways could use new paint and touchups. We were there for 6 days, there are two "tiny" elevators, one was out of service our entire stay, it's an 8 story hotel, so you either wait in queue to go into the elevator or use the stairway! Lastly, i have never stayed in a hotel, where i had to go out and buy cleaning products to clean the smell of urine from the bathroom, but i had to, our's smelled so bad it was unbearable. When i talked to the girl at the desk about the issue, she was indifferent, as if i shouldn't have really been complaining. My family and i will one day return to Paris, but NEVER back to this property. The Citadines greatly disappoints!!

Had to request room change rooms due to clogged shower drain but front desk staff (Melody) very helpful put us in great room with balcony and Eiffel Tower view. Excellent location in great area with metro station in front of hotel.

This hotel has a great location, comfortable beds, quiet, insulated windows, view of Eiffel Tower, full kitchen, lots of space to put things & a little sitting area. Extras were free coffee any time of day, umbrellas, dishwashing soap, a clothesline in tub.

The hotel was clean. Room was spacious and comfortable. Breakfast was good as well. The staff was helpful and accommodating.

There's a metro station right outside the hotel which made it easy to get around.

This was the perfect spot for our vacation. I went with my kids. There's a train station across the street, a Monoprix next door, which seems to have everything we forgot and groceries and a McDonald's downstairs and sushi next door as well. There were plenty of cafe's along the walk to the Eiffel tower and food is amazing around there. It was a very short walk to the Eiffel Tower. I didn't time it, but my kids did just fine with no complaints to get there. We had a view of the Eiffel Tower and it was a nice surprise because I wasn't expecting it. I understand that only certain rooms in the hotel have that view and I inquired ahead of time and they said they couldn't accommodate. I LOVED the fact that on Sunday there was a farmer's market that popped up in front of the hotel. Delicious food and fruit! Since you have a little kitchen and a little refrigerator, take advantage! I read all the reviews for this hotel before choosing it and I'm glad I did. You have to go into the reservation KNOWING that it's not like regular hotel. You're not going to have daily cleaning unless you pay for it, it's like an extended stay. You're not gonna have a pool. But we were fine with all that because the price was reasonable in comparison to the other hotels in Paris.... and because we knew what it was, they exceeded our expectations. The rooms are spacious. The pullout couch was really neat because it pulled out into two small beds, not a double like they normally are. My boys enjoyed having their own beds. I liked the free coffee downstairs as well and also the fact that we could do laundry for a very small fee. I traveled with the kids by myself, so I needed to travel light. We only brought a few clothes and did laundry before we headed out to Disneyland Paris. The staff is very friendly and very helpful when I needed to find something for us to eat so late at night on the day of our arrival. Thank you for a great stay!

I must admit I was a little apprehensive about an apar-hotel,as well as the location. Well, if I ever have the opportunity to visit Paris again, this is will be my choice. The reception staff were amazingly helpful and all spoke fluent English. Josephina and Djenny could not have been more friendly. It was immaculate and just what we, 2 women traveling without our husbands,needed. It was directly across the street from the Metro. So traveling throughout Paris was easy and safe. Several good restaurants and bakeries were within our block. As well as 2 grocers,Monoprix and Franprix. And of course you would guess from the name , an easy stroll to the beautiful Eiffel Tower.

Loved the size of the room and we only had a studio however you can get alot of background rumble noise from trains. We had a room well back aswell. Room 204. I'll try and attach 3 photos. Would I stay again? Yes maybe for 1 - 2 nights because it is walking distance to the Eiffel tower. More nights and the train noise could get to you. We stayed 4 nights and it started to bother us. No problem if you are a deep sleeper or want to experience what it is like for millions of people who live near train lines like you see in the romantic movies. It's got very good 3.5 star furnishings, and if the price is kept down then it is... OK. We liked how it is bigger than a standard hotel room. The studio had a decent kitchenette aswell which was a real plus. So, it's a very good average place and if you are a good sleeper then it's OK but not good if you are a light sleeper.
Only a minority of rooms will have some Eiffel tower views. Top floors etc however they will also face the train line below.

Very nice apartment, well organised and fantastic location. The only thing I didn't liked that we didn't receive rooms cleaning next day which was very important for me with two little kids. The rest every thing was great.

Website over represents the rooms on pictures. Amazing location, very friendly staff, very average rooms. They charged nearly $450 for a room with a view of an Eiffel tower, however the amenities inside the room were very BLAH to say the least. When we arrived with our two kids at nearly 10pm, the beds for them were not made. Very cheap bedding, pillows, blankets etc. The rooms are at best 3+ star amenity , at a lot heftier price.

Though it's a little out of the city the hotel is close to a Metro station and bus stop and only 12 minutes walk to the Eiffel tour (a cab from the Eurostar station cost us about 15 Euro which, for the convenience was great). Our room was a decent size, was very stylish and modern and clean. The bathroom is great, with a bath which was lovely. The kitchen area is a good size with everything we needed for our stay - including a dishwasher so we weren't washing up all the time. The room was serviced once during our stay, which was perfect. The staff are very friendly and helpful and I believe the front desk is manned 24 hours. You can book various tours and tickets through the front desk which is handy - you pay slightly more but the convenience is good.

Stayed here for 2 nights. The hotel has a great location and is just 10-15 min walk from the eiffel tower. The metro station is also right in front of the hotel which gives an easy access to all the sights around paris. The staff at the reception is extremely helpful with sugesstions on places to visit and how to get to them in the cheapest and best way.

The rooms are quite spacious and comfortable. The only reason i wouldnt give this place 5 stars is because I was really dissapointed when I saw the towels in the bathroom and the bedsheets.
The towels in our room had 1-2 strands of hair stuck to it and also some spots (maybe makeup) and the same was on the pillows and blancket.

The cleanliness could have been better.

This hotel was absolutely amazing! The staff were extremely friendly and helpful at all times. The rooms were very clean and presented nicely with the beds made and a very well kept kitchenette. The breakfast offered was very nice with a wide range of foods available.
Overall it was a great stay and I could recommend it to anyone.

Stayed at the Citadines hotel in Paris for a week. It was a great experience.

The hotel was very conveniently located and near most of the sites in Paris. It was within a 15 minute walking distance of the Eiffel Tower.

The 2 room apartment was just perfect for us. It was clean and very well maintained. The morning breakfast was great as well.

Special thanks to Eric Chabalgoity at the front desk who was extremely helpful with all our questions. He pointed out the best restaurants and the places to visit. Eric’s help is much appreciated.

Director Fabienne Higele and Adriem Sardini are running an superhotel.

Kudos to all of you.

Will definitely be back.

This hotel saved us from a terrible Airbnb experience. The location is perfect! Just teo blocks away from the Eiffel tower lawn and rifht in front from a Subway line (wich might be an issue for rooms facing it but it was no problem for us, as our room faced another street. The rooms where big and had a full kitchen, balcony, closet and all needed amenities and tolettirss. We were able to get as much toilettries, towels and sheets as needed and a washing/dryingroom was available for us to use at a very moderate price. Room service was not included, which shouls have, for the price of the room, that’s the only reason why we’ve given it a 4 put of 5 stars.

I stayed at this hotel for about one month with my university history class. It was the perfect location, clean, friendly staff and felt like home. The kitchens in the rooms are really helpful to keep you from eating out every single meal, and if you want to eat any sort of salad that consists of lettuce in France (otherwise a salad is cheese and bread). The rooms are spacious and clean. My room had a nice cozy view of the courtyard, but some of my classmates had a nice view of the Eiffel Tower. There is so much to see and do with in minutes of walking, and the metro is literally right outside the hotel to get around the city. I would happily love to return here when I come back to Paris! Highly recommend!

The hotel location is good and it is apartment style but it is expensive and service is normal

If you are looking for hotel in center and you don’t care about lux hotel, it is the right one despite the expensive rate

Metro is just few steps away and many restaurants around in addition to 5 minutes walk to Efil tower

- coffee machine and tea is available at lobby free of charge

Our 5 night stay was delightful. It was well worth paying extra for the views! The apartment was clean, the bed comfortable and the little kitchenette had everything we needed. The staff was very helpful answering our many questions and providing us with a map and also a list of common tourist attraction with directions on how to get there from the hotel. In the hotel lobby there is a wonderful coffee machine with cappuccinos, espressos and hot chocolate. There is also an cold water machine. The elevator was quick, never having to wait for long. The subway station was right across the street. This is in the 15th arrondissement which is a residential area with many cafes and restaurants, a bakery a few blocks away where we got our daily pain au chocolat ( yum!) and a grocery store just across the street,Very convenient for traveling through Paris! We would definitely stay there again!

Convenient and safety location, all the staffs willing to answer questions and help us to solved the problem.Some of tea or coffee free for us. If i have free time, that hotel must be the first choice to choose when i coming paria again.
